Previously stated, although size distribution of QDs can be controlled for specific applications exploiting precise fabrication techniques, they still impose some limitations on the gain characteristics of SOA structure. With the size of QDs restricted, IHB can take specific values as ΓG so that the maximum size distribution over a specific radius R0, denoted as ΔRmax, gives the maximum ΓG. Following this result, one can figure out the minimum N necessary to produce the desired ultra-broadband gain output. As Fig. 3(A) depicts, over a specific Eg0\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
